          Dublin's medieval core survives in fragments scattered through the modern city. Christ Church Cathedral, founded in 1030, contains a crypt dating to the original Viking-era construction‚Äîthe oldest surviving structure in Dublin. The crypt has been in continuous use for nearly a thousand years and contains artifacts ranging from a mummified cat and rat (trapped in a pipe for centuries) to stocks used for public punishment.
        </p>
              <div class="my-8 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
